Property.Value: This world configuration demonstrates the effect of extreme biome volatility levels. Uses a single biome with custom height and volatility settings. In the world settings all biomes but one have been removed from Biome Groups, only the NormalBiomes group remains with a single biome. Border biomes and Isle biomes list are empty to prevent other biomes from spawning. LandRarity set to 100 to prevent oceans from spawning. In the biome settings height and volatility have been changed. For this example rivers and vanilla structures have been disabled via the world settings. Resources (ores, trees etc) have been disabled via the ResourceQueue biome setting. Pre-generator and world border radius are at 5 chunks. Reminds me of a level from that classic old game Worms!
